### 2\. Getting Started

#### 2.2. Becoming a Graduate Teaching Assistant (GTA)

A Graduate Teaching Assistant (GTA) is a student (usually a PhD student, but sometimes MSc and final year undergraduate students) who undertakes some form of teaching and/or educational support on a casual basis within their departments.

As a TA, you are an integral part of a departmental teaching team and highly valued by the students you are teaching, and the academic staff you work with. Being a TA can involve a wide variety of different roles:

* Demonstrating in labs
* leading seminars/small group teaching;
* taking tutorials;
* problem classes;
* delivering feedback;
* marking students' work

Further information about being a GTA can be found [here](https://emckclac.sharepoint.com/sites/KPRH/SitePages/Doctoral_Teaching.aspx).

If you are interested in undertaking this work then please visit [King's Teachers](https://kingsteachers.kcl.ac.uk/) to sign up!

